  "ingredientsTitle": "Ingredients",
  "ingredientGroups": [
   {
    "title": null,
    "items": [
     "250  ml coconut<br>",
     "500 ml oats<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-040.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-040-768x1024.jpg\" title=\"Oat crunchies - still a favourite\" alt=\"Coq Au Vin en oatskoekies blog 040\" class=\"direction-step-image\" loading=\"lazy\"></a>",
     "250 ml cake flour<br>",
     "250 ml sugar (brown or white)<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-042.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><br><img src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-042-1024x768.jpg\" title=\"Oat crunchies - still a favourite\" alt=\"Coq Au Vin en oatskoekies blog 042\" class=\"direction-step-image\" loading=\"lazy\"></a><br>",
     "5 ml bicarbonate of soda",
     "60 ml peanut butter",
     "60 ml golden syrup",
     "250 ml butter<br>",
     "pinch of salt"
    ]
   }
  ],
  "directionsTitle": "Method",
  "directionGroups": [
   {
    "title": null,
    "steps": [
     "Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.",
     "Mix the flour, sugar, coconut, oats, bicarbonate of soda and salt in a mixing bowl.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-045.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-045.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"Coq Au Vin en oatskoekies blog 045\" title=\"Oat crunchies - still a favourite\"></a>",
     "Melt the butter, peanut butter and syrup in the microwave (for about a minute).",
     "Now stir the butter mixture well through your dry ingredients.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-050.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-050.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"Coq Au Vin en oatskoekies blog 050\" title=\"Oat crunchies - still a favourite\"></a>",
     "Spray a baking tray or oven dish with Spray and Cook.",
     "Press the oat mixture firmly into your dish &#8211; using your hands works best.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-054.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1125\" height=\"1500\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-054.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"Coq Au Vin en oatskoekies blog 054\" title=\"Oat crunchies - still a favourite\"></a>",
     "Bake for 25 minutes until golden brown on top.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-058.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-058.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"Coq Au Vin en oatskoekies blog 058\" title=\"Oat crunchies - still a favourite\"></a>",
     "As soon as it comes out of the oven, cut it into blocks immediately and leave it in the dish to cool.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-062.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1125\" height=\"1500\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/Coq-Au-Vin-en-oatskoekies-blog-062.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"Coq Au Vin en oatskoekies blog 062\" title=\"Oat crunchies - still a favourite\"></a>"
    ]
   }
  ],
  "notesTitle": "Notes",
  "notes": [
   "This is a delicious little snack, or something to pop into the kids' lunchboxes. Be warned, once you start eating you won't be able to stop."
